        "timestamp": "2020-07-09 12:54:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi,\n\nThis commit intends to refactor CsarUtils::addInnerComponentsToCSAR by introducing a ZipIO type. This type describes an operation performing a write in a Zip file while abstracting the writing logic (done by ZipIO.ZipWriter). The main benefit is separation of concerns, testability and composition. On the long term, we should be able to express most of the operations done in CsarUtils using this type while getting rid of the IOExceptions and significantly improve testability and maintenance.\n\nThank you in advance for your help,\n\nFrancis.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
